<div><h3>SPAN 243 - Latin American Essay and Thought </h3>  <p><hr>A study of Latin-American thought from the nineteenth through twenty-first centuries. Explores issues of identity (national, group and personal) and how politics, class, gender, ethnicity and race affect cultural production. We will sample a variety of forms of public opinion. Students will seek current topics in Latin America.</p>

